1
00:00:05,844 --> 00:00:08,580
♫ I want to go to the future ♫

2
00:00:08,580 --> 00:00:12,135
♫  Time bears witness to my quirkiness  ♫

3
00:00:12,135 --> 00:00:18,328
♫ I want to seize the day And put the whole world into my head ♫

4
00:00:18,328 --> 00:00:24,554
♫ I want to go back in time To do all the crazy things I didn't do ♫

5
00:00:24,554 --> 00:00:30,975
♫ Don't say goodbye And don't glaze. All the lights are lit up ♫

6
00:00:30,975 --> 00:00:35,961
♫ We are always looking forward
to the unknown future ♫

7
00:00:35,961 --> 00:00:43,361
♫  And often overlooking our surroundings and best plan in front of us  ♫

8
00:00:43,361 --> 00:00:48,285
♫ Every day my heart beats for you ♫

9
00:00:48,285 --> 00:00:49,898
♫  Be your light  ♫

10
00:00:49,898 --> 00:00:55,661
♫  You are no doubt irreplaceable  ♫

11
00:00:55,661 --> 00:01:02,161
♫ Every day the sun shines through the window ♫

12
00:01:02,161 --> 00:01:08,528
♫  With your reflection being my incredible highlight  ♫

13
00:01:08,528 --> 00:01:11,469
[I Don't Want to be Brothers with You]

14
00:01:16,380 --> 00:01:19,419
Beibei, why aren't you packing things up after school?

15
00:01:19,419 --> 00:01:24,679
Xiaowen, well, shall we go play WOW later?

16
00:01:24,679 --> 00:01:26,120
What's WOW?

17
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:29,305
World of Warcraft 3: Frozen Throne, you don't know it?

18
00:01:30,619 --> 00:01:31,740
I'm not going.

19
00:01:31,740 --> 00:01:34,840
I think you don't know how to play it, right?

20
00:01:34,840 --> 00:01:37,859
Don't worry. I won't crush you, Bro. I'll teach you.

21
00:01:37,859 --> 00:01:41,939
I said I wasn't going. Don't call me Bro.

22
00:01:43,879 --> 00:01:46,440
- Gao Yang, come to my place for dinner.
- No.

23
00:01:46,440 --> 00:01:49,579
What would you eat then? Uncle Gao isn't home.

24
00:01:49,579 --> 00:01:51,877
Xiaowen will make dinner.

25
00:01:51,877 --> 00:01:56,919
What can he make? We're having vegetable rice wraps tonight.

26
00:01:56,919 --> 00:02:00,200
That's so ordinary. Xiaowen can make a lot of dishes.

27
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:02,900
Double cooked pork slices, sauteed three vegetables, and stewed pork ribs.

28
00:02:02,900 --> 00:02:04,650
I can't make these.

29
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:10,580
What do you mean you can't make them? I want to eat them. Please make them for me.

30
00:02:10,580 --> 00:02:13,340
If anything, I'll call you Big Brother.

31
00:02:13,340 --> 00:02:15,680
- I'll go eat at your place too.
- What are you going to do then?

32
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:19,360
How about this? Jiabao, Meng, we'll have a get-together at his place tonight.

33
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:20,819
Sure, sure.

34
00:02:20,819 --> 00:02:24,680
A get-together? I'll go invite Mi Jia.

35
00:02:33,882 --> 00:02:38,300
[Episode 5: We're Brothers]

36
00:02:47,140 --> 00:02:48,600
Piao Jiutong?

37
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:52,810
I know him. He's the Leader of the Korean Interest Group.

38
00:02:52,810 --> 00:02:55,780
His family sells sporting goods. He sells them here too.

39
00:02:55,780 --> 00:03:01,120
- His nickname is Supermarket of No. 3 High School.
- I think he's super annoying.

40
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:04,319
What's wrong, Mi Jia? Did he bully you?

41
00:03:05,180 --> 00:03:11,159
If he ever dares to bully you, remember to bring up my name. I'll put him in his place.

42
00:03:11,159 --> 00:03:15,700
It's okay, Xiaowen. Just do the best you can. If it doesn't taste good, I live right upstairs.

43
00:03:15,700 --> 00:03:17,240
I can bring some dishes down.

44
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:19,579
You won't have that chance.

45
00:03:35,380 --> 00:03:38,014
- Mr. Gao. You're off work?
- Yes.

46
00:03:49,919 --> 00:03:54,060
How is it? I told you Xiaowen is a great cook. It's a perfect combination of color, aroma, and taste.

47
00:03:54,060 --> 00:03:57,059
He didn't even show 50% of his real talent.

48
00:03:57,059 --> 00:03:59,659
- Is this the last dish?
- Let's eat.

49
00:04:01,220 --> 00:04:02,923
Zhao Jiabao!

50
00:04:04,200 --> 00:04:06,500
You're so impolite.

51
00:04:09,979 --> 00:04:12,300
You should eat first then.

52
00:04:12,300 --> 00:04:14,140
I'm not eating.

53
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:23,679
Come on, eat. Xiaowen is a great cook. It'll be all gone later.

54
00:04:23,679 --> 00:04:25,600
That's right.

55
00:04:28,399 --> 00:04:30,679
It's okay. Meng, start eating.

56
00:04:32,540 --> 00:04:36,179
Try it. It's delicious. Try it. Come on.

57
00:04:49,399 --> 00:04:50,680
What's wrong?

58
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:52,920
My mom's cooking doesn't taste good anymore.

59
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:55,000
- Let's eat.
- Let's eat, everyone.

60
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:57,020
Go home soon after dinner. We still have school tomorrow.

61
00:04:57,020 --> 00:04:59,317
That's right. Hurry and eat.

62
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:03,700
Beibei, aren't you going to eat?

63
00:05:03,700 --> 00:05:05,469
I'm not hungry.

64
00:05:19,199 --> 00:05:22,259
- Xiaowen, go grab the vinegar.
- Okay

65
00:05:25,940 --> 00:05:27,765
Eat more.

66
00:05:28,414 --> 00:05:31,000
- Can you reach that?
- Yes.

67
00:05:42,160 --> 00:05:43,700
Hubby, I'm home.

68
00:05:43,700 --> 00:05:46,619
- You're home, Wifey!
- Yes, yes.

69
00:05:46,619 --> 00:05:48,939
Come on, lean on me. Change into your slippers, Wifey.

70
00:05:48,939 --> 00:05:51,279
Come on. What do you want for dinner? I'll cook it for you.

71
00:05:51,279 --> 00:05:53,718
Xiaowen has already made dinner.

72
00:05:59,539 --> 00:06:02,760
Well, Beibei, it was my fault for yelling at you last time.

73
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:04,920
I'll ask Xiaowen to leave now.

74
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:08,139
No, don't! Xiaowen can live here as long as he wants.

75
00:06:08,139 --> 00:06:10,163
Come on. Sit down and eat with us.

76
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:13,300
Come on, come on.

77
00:06:13,300 --> 00:06:15,680
This is double cooked pork slices.

78
00:06:16,260 --> 00:06:18,940
Gao Yang, learn a few dishes from Xiaowen when you have time.

79
00:06:18,940 --> 00:06:22,820
Don't eat at my place all the time. Xiaowen, eat more.

80
00:06:23,540 --> 00:06:25,279
Beibei,

81
00:06:25,279 --> 00:06:27,360
shouldn't you make a toast to Xiaowen?

82
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:29,273
Sure.

83
00:06:29,273 --> 00:06:33,660
Xiaowen, generally speaking, I should make a toast to you for making dinner today.

84
00:06:33,660 --> 00:06:39,680
Here's the thing. I will give a warm welcome to Xiaowen on behalf of Gao Yang for your arrival at the Gao's residence

85
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:42,250
- Come on.
- Cheers! Cheers!

86
00:06:44,920 --> 00:06:46,000
- Mr. Gao.
- Hi, Mr. Gao.

87
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:48,449
- You're all here?
- Uncle Gao.

88
00:06:48,449 --> 00:06:51,319
There're so many dishes here. Who made them? Beibei, did you make them?

89
00:06:51,319 --> 00:06:54,439
Mr. Gao, I can't cook. Xiaowen made them.

90
00:06:54,439 --> 00:06:56,620
Good job, Xiaowen. I didn't know you are so talented.

91
00:06:56,620 --> 00:06:58,630
Why did you come home?

92
00:07:03,700 --> 00:07:09,819
Did you drink too much? Why are you speaking gibberish? This is my house. Why can't I come back?

93
00:07:10,779 --> 00:07:14,380
Uncle Gao, you didn't bring us any tasty treats from your trip to Beijing?

94
00:07:14,380 --> 00:07:17,170
For someone so attentive like me, of course, I would.

95
00:07:17,759 --> 00:07:21,340
- What's this?
- Beijing Roast Duck!

96
00:07:22,190 --> 00:07:24,287
I'm full.

97
00:07:24,287 --> 00:07:26,739
That's not how you open it.

98
00:07:26,739 --> 00:07:30,220
Gao Yang, you're not eating the roast duck?

99
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:35,260
What the hell is it? What roast duck? You could tell he bought it from the train station.

100
00:07:35,260 --> 00:07:38,460
What else can it be if it's not a roast duck? Is it braised chicken?

101
00:07:38,460 --> 00:07:41,660
What's wrong with you, Gao Yang? Why are you so irritable today?

102
00:07:41,660 --> 00:07:44,059
You said you'd be back in a few days. How many days has it been?

103
00:07:44,059 --> 00:07:45,059
What are you doing?

104
00:07:45,059 --> 00:07:49,940
Why shouldn't I be angry? You left so suddenly. Now you're back. What do you mean?

105
00:07:49,940 --> 00:07:54,280
Did I go on vacation? I went to a conference. It's work! Do you understand?

106
00:07:54,280 --> 00:07:58,460
Work? That's all you talk about. Work, work, work! Did you make any money? Where's the money?

107
00:07:58,460 --> 00:08:00,626
Mr. Gao.

108
00:08:00,626 --> 00:08:03,260
Mr. Gao, we'll be on our way then.

109
00:08:03,260 --> 00:08:05,219
Why are you leaving? There's still so much food left.

110
00:08:05,219 --> 00:08:07,539
- We're full.
- We're all full.

111
00:08:07,539 --> 00:08:09,736
- The duck is...
- Shut your mouth.

112
00:08:10,380 --> 00:08:12,480
- All right then.
- Okay, okay.

113
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:14,439
- Be careful on your way home.
- Go back.
- Okay.

114
00:08:14,439 --> 00:08:16,000
- Don't worry.
- Jiabao, walk them home.

115
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:18,620
- Bye, Mr. Gao.
- Bye.

116
00:08:18,620 --> 00:08:21,459
- The duck...
- Let's go!

117
00:08:34,759 --> 00:08:36,361
Xiaowen,

118
00:08:36,919 --> 00:08:42,403
I'm sorry. I ruined your nice get-together.

119
00:08:43,459 --> 00:08:46,819
No, we finished anyway.

120
00:08:49,679 --> 00:08:51,279
Gao Yang, come out here.

121
00:08:51,279 --> 00:08:52,279
I'm not coming out.

122
00:08:52,279 --> 00:08:54,399
I'll smack you.

123
00:08:55,399 --> 00:09:00,220
Come on, smack me. Show Xiaowen how you usually treat me.

124
00:09:00,980 --> 00:09:03,819
Fine. Sit down.

125
00:09:03,819 --> 00:09:07,899
Don't pull a long face. Let's have a nice chat, okay?

126
00:09:11,900 --> 00:09:14,420
Chat about what? About Xiaowen?

127
00:09:14,420 --> 00:09:18,379
We'll talk about Xiaowen another day. Let's talk about you today.

128
00:09:18,379 --> 00:09:19,980
I'll go clean up.

129
00:09:19,980 --> 00:09:24,020
Xiaowen, take a seat. You're not an outsider.

130
00:09:24,799 --> 00:09:30,799
Gao Yang, let's both hold our temper in front of Xiaowen today.

131
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:35,320
How about this? I'll apologize to you first.

132
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:38,240
Over the years, I've made a lot of mistakes.

133
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:42,259
What do you mean by this, Gao Bin? Are you pretending to be a good father in front of an outsider?

134
00:09:42,259 --> 00:09:46,339
Don't be sarcastic. I'm trying to communicate with you.

135
00:09:46,339 --> 00:09:50,160
You always say I don't listen to you. Have you ever listened to me?

136
00:09:50,160 --> 00:09:52,518
Fine, go ahead.

137
00:09:53,519 --> 00:09:54,998
Gao Yang,

138
00:09:55,539 --> 00:10:01,940
I know you want to go to Beijing. However, you'll be taking the college entrance exam soon.

139
00:10:02,039 --> 00:10:03,200
The college entrance exam

140
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:04,720
is a crucial point in your life.

141
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:07,040
You need family by your side.

142
00:10:07,040 --> 00:10:08,707
If you go to Beijing,

143
00:10:08,707 --> 00:10:10,740
what can your mom do for you besides giving you money?

144
00:10:10,740 --> 00:10:11,980
Wait, why are you bringing my mom into this?

145
00:10:11,980 --> 00:10:14,310
That's exactly what I'm talking about!

146
00:10:18,120 --> 00:10:20,313
I'll be honest with you.

147
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:24,292
I didn't even get to see your mother when I was in Beijing.

148
00:10:24,292 --> 00:10:25,779
Do you think she has time

149
00:10:25,779 --> 00:10:28,412
to take care of you if you're there?

150
00:10:28,412 --> 00:10:30,080
That's none of your business.

151
00:10:30,080 --> 00:10:31,759
Gao Yang.

152
00:10:31,759 --> 00:10:33,699
Are these from my mom?

153
00:10:33,699 --> 00:10:36,113
Your mom asked someone to pass them to me.

154
00:10:37,879 --> 00:10:39,719
A PlayStation console.

155
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:44,679
Gao Yang, put that down. Let's talk first, okay?

156
00:10:46,279 --> 00:10:47,988
Gao Yang.

157
00:10:52,899 --> 00:10:54,880
Gao Yang, come on.

158
00:10:54,880 --> 00:10:56,360
Give the game console to me first.

159
00:10:56,360 --> 00:10:58,440
What are you doing? I'm going to play the game.

160
00:10:58,440 --> 00:11:00,799
Can't you play after we talk?

161
00:11:00,799 --> 00:11:02,519
Can you give that to me first? Let's have a chat.

162
00:11:02,519 --> 00:11:04,060
I don't have anything to say to you.

163
00:11:04,060 --> 00:11:06,639
Why can't you listen to me?

164
00:11:06,639 --> 00:11:09,719
Are you crazy? Why did you smash it?

165
00:11:15,539 --> 00:11:17,972
Just say what you want to say!

166
00:11:30,900 --> 00:11:33,318
Your mom wants to transfer you to another school.

167
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,696
I refused.

168
00:11:37,960 --> 00:11:40,620
That's not up to you. Move away.

169
00:11:51,420 --> 00:11:53,366
I'll go smoke a cigarette in my room.

170
00:12:58,420 --> 00:12:59,760
What happened?

171
00:12:59,760 --> 00:13:01,711
The circuit tripped.

172
00:13:01,711 --> 00:13:04,059
Nothing good happens when you come home.

173
00:13:04,059 --> 00:13:06,450
Move the light this way.

174
00:13:07,480 --> 00:13:10,800
Which d*mn kid stole the safety fuse?

175
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:12,819
Why did they steal yours and not anyone else's?

176
00:13:12,819 --> 00:13:14,760
You're so popular.

177
00:13:15,720 --> 00:13:18,000
All thanks to you and your temper.

178
00:13:19,039 --> 00:13:21,240
Xiaowen, the safety fuse.

179
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:30,759
Learn from Xiaowen. He's such an obedient boy.

180
00:13:30,759 --> 00:13:32,519
Do you want the light or not?

181
00:13:32,519 --> 00:13:34,371
Hurry up.

182
00:13:38,459 --> 00:13:40,320
Can you do it or not?

183
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:41,879
If you can't, let me do it.

184
00:13:41,879 --> 00:13:43,559
Why must you brag about everything?

185
00:13:43,559 --> 00:13:44,679
Do you know how to do it?

186
00:13:44,679 --> 00:13:46,340
What if you get electrocuted?

187
00:13:46,340 --> 00:13:48,039
How would I tell your mom?

188
00:13:48,039 --> 00:13:49,865
Hurry up.

189
00:13:53,370 --> 00:13:55,673
[Live and Work Well]

190
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:16,420
The game console...

191
00:14:16,420 --> 00:14:18,459
It already fell apart. We should just toss it away.

192
00:14:18,459 --> 00:14:20,772
I think it can still be fixed.

193
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:24,539
I'll bring it to the store to get it fixed then.

194
00:14:24,539 --> 00:14:26,239
Don't fix it.

195
00:14:26,879 --> 00:14:28,399
I don't like that anyway.

196
00:14:28,399 --> 00:14:31,059
Besides, buy yourself some drinks if you have money.

197
00:14:31,059 --> 00:14:32,579
I'm going to bed.

198
00:14:37,159 --> 00:14:39,359
Xiaowen, get some rest soon.

199
00:14:40,459 --> 00:14:42,290
Mr. Gao,

200
00:14:43,520 --> 00:14:46,530
the two of you can talk nicely.

201
00:14:58,370 --> 00:15:00,090
[No Entry for Jin Doudou]

202
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:02,845
Sis,

203
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:07,200
I'll treat you to some snacks.

204
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:09,159
You're treating me?

205
00:15:09,159 --> 00:15:10,480
Why would you be so nice?

206
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:13,560
Aren't you my sister?

207
00:15:13,560 --> 00:15:15,120
They must be expired.

208
00:15:15,120 --> 00:15:18,199
No, I just bought them.

209
00:15:19,120 --> 00:15:21,020
That's more like it.

210
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:27,840
Does it taste good?

211
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:29,120
It's all right.

212
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:30,679
Doesn't this taste like

213
00:15:30,679 --> 00:15:33,519
the coins in your piggy bank?

214
00:15:33,519 --> 00:15:35,079
Jin Doudou!

215
00:15:35,079 --> 00:15:37,740
Tom, Tom, I'm Jerry! Come and get me.

216
00:15:37,740 --> 00:15:39,579
It's so late at night. I don't want to argue with you.

217
00:15:39,579 --> 00:15:41,513
I'll go tell mom and dad.

218
00:15:43,519 --> 00:15:45,679
Bin is still too impulsive.

219
00:15:45,679 --> 00:15:47,639
He can't even handle Gao Yang.

220
00:15:47,639 --> 00:15:48,799
Now, there's Xiaowen too.

221
00:15:48,799 --> 00:15:50,579
He brought him home.

222
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:53,840
He and Xiaowen's mom...

223
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:56,319
After all, they have that kind of relationship...

224
00:15:57,480 --> 00:16:01,800
Yes, but Xiaowen might not know about it.

225
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:03,679
Bin is supposed to face that issue.

226
00:16:03,679 --> 00:16:05,519
Since he's raising Xiaowen now,

227
00:16:05,519 --> 00:16:08,419
it means he recognizes him as a son.

228
00:16:11,900 --> 00:16:13,623
What?

229
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:28,099
Who would steal

230
00:16:28,099 --> 00:16:30,559
the safety fuse for fun?

231
00:16:33,719 --> 00:16:35,715
By the way, Xiaowen,

232
00:16:37,340 --> 00:16:39,380
have you been to Beijing?

233
00:16:40,340 --> 00:16:41,933
No.

234
00:16:46,039 --> 00:16:47,779
Do you...

235
00:16:47,779 --> 00:16:50,132
really want to transfer to another school?

236
00:16:51,640 --> 00:16:53,232
By the way,

237
00:16:54,539 --> 00:16:55,799
Gao Bin said

238
00:16:55,799 --> 00:16:57,699
we'd talk about you another day.

239
00:16:57,699 --> 00:16:59,361
What's that?

240
00:17:00,620 --> 00:17:02,640
I-It's nothing.

241
00:17:03,440 --> 00:17:04,599
Gao Yang!

242
00:17:04,599 --> 00:17:06,019
Answer the phone!

243
00:17:06,019 --> 00:17:07,574
Coming!

244
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:10,680
What is it?

245
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:12,380
Gao Yang, I'm going to tell you something.

246
00:17:12,380 --> 00:17:13,780
You have to stay calm.

247
00:17:13,780 --> 00:17:15,635
Ye Xiaowen is...

248
00:17:18,019 --> 00:17:19,079
What happened?

249
00:17:19,079 --> 00:17:20,200
I don't know.

250
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:21,894
She suddenly went quiet.

251
00:17:23,380 --> 00:17:24,359
Dad.

252
00:17:24,359 --> 00:17:26,019
I don't care what you've heard.

253
00:17:26,019 --> 00:17:27,459
Keep it to yourself.

254
00:17:27,459 --> 00:17:29,620
Do not say a word to Gao Yang.

255
00:17:29,620 --> 00:17:31,559
But Ye Xiaowen is Uncle Gao's...

256
00:17:31,559 --> 00:17:33,361
Go to sleep.

257
00:17:38,380 --> 00:17:40,800
Doudou, go to sleep now.

258
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:50,459
Let me tell you, just use a human character.

259
00:17:50,459 --> 00:17:54,300
Do you know what this year's World e-Sports Games champion Li Xiaofeng used?

260
00:17:54,300 --> 00:17:56,459
He used a human character.

261
00:17:56,459 --> 00:17:59,639
I think he'll be the champion again next year. Let me tell you...

262
00:17:59,639 --> 00:18:01,640
- Come out for a second.
- What?

263
00:18:01,640 --> 00:18:03,837
I want to tell you something.

264
00:18:03,837 --> 00:18:05,532
What is it?

265
00:18:06,799 --> 00:18:07,880
About last night.

266
00:18:07,880 --> 00:18:09,000
Just say it here.

267
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:11,280
Come out now.

268
00:18:11,280 --> 00:18:14,179
I'm telling him about the game.

269
00:18:14,880 --> 00:18:17,294
Beibei, come have some grilled cold noodles.

270
00:18:25,079 --> 00:18:27,839
Zhao Jiabao!

271
00:18:27,839 --> 00:18:29,419
I'll buy you another bowl.

272
00:18:29,419 --> 00:18:32,499
It's not about the cold noodles!

273
00:18:32,499 --> 00:18:34,880
So annoying!

274
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:36,480
Ignore her. I'm already used to it.

275
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:38,370
Let's continue.

276
00:18:38,370 --> 00:18:42,830
[Fix any electronic problems]

277
00:18:50,279 --> 00:18:52,035
What do you want to fix?

278
00:18:54,680 --> 00:18:56,546
How much would it cost to fix this?

279
00:18:57,607 --> 00:18:58,960
I can't fix it.

280
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:00,400
Why not?

281
00:19:00,400 --> 00:19:02,000
I took time off work to come here.

282
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:04,449
It's too fancy. I don't know how to fix it.

283
00:19:07,440 --> 00:19:09,279
How much is it to buy a new one?

284
00:19:09,279 --> 00:19:10,279
Two thousand.

285
00:19:10,279 --> 00:19:12,000
Why is it so expensive?

286
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:14,499
Even so, we don't have it in stock.

287
00:19:21,960 --> 00:19:23,514
I'll take one.

288
00:19:24,920 --> 00:19:27,225
You really want it?

289
00:19:27,225 --> 00:19:30,160
Bro, your child must love you very much.

290
00:19:30,160 --> 00:19:32,079
Not a lot of people in Tieyuan can afford to play this.

291
00:19:32,079 --> 00:19:33,863
I'll write you a receipt.

292
00:19:35,160 --> 00:19:37,188
This is the one I want.

293
00:19:40,559 --> 00:19:42,185
Ninety-nine Yuan.

294
00:19:44,039 --> 00:19:45,480
Give me two game discs.

295
00:19:45,480 --> 00:19:47,442
The kind that carries a hundred games on it.

296
00:19:49,140 --> 00:19:53,760
What are the wrong usages of this idiom?

297
00:19:53,760 --> 00:19:58,279
One of them is called taking it too literally and making subjective assumptions.

298
00:19:58,279 --> 00:19:59,480
What does that mean?

299
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:00,039
What are you writing?

300
00:20:00,039 --> 00:20:03,160
That means you didn't understand what the idiom means,

301
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:04,080
Keep learning.

302
00:20:04,080 --> 00:20:07,599
before you came up with a concept subjectively and used it in the wrong context.

303
00:20:07,599 --> 00:20:09,760
For example, the idiom "ten thousand empty alleys",

304
00:20:09,760 --> 00:20:13,140
a lot of people would think it means this place is completely empty.

305
00:20:13,140 --> 00:20:14,799
That's not true.

306
00:20:14,799 --> 00:20:17,279
What's the complete meaning of the idiom? It means when something is very popular,

307
00:20:17,279 --> 00:20:21,165
everyone is showing up to see it, which caused the entire town to be empty.

308
00:20:22,079 --> 00:20:24,839
For the idiom "a groundless rumor"...

309
00:20:24,839 --> 00:20:26,797
Gao Yang.

310
00:20:29,759 --> 00:20:31,519
What are you doing?

311
00:20:32,739 --> 00:20:34,892
I'm asking you. What are you doing?

312
00:20:35,440 --> 00:20:36,939
Nothing.

313
00:20:36,939 --> 00:20:39,345
Which idiom was I talking about?

314
00:20:39,345 --> 00:20:40,400
A groundless rumor.

315
00:20:40,400 --> 00:20:42,889
A peacock gone mad.

316
00:20:42,889 --> 00:20:44,781
I think you've gone mad.

317
00:20:49,780 --> 00:20:51,812
Where's your school uniform?

318
00:20:51,812 --> 00:20:55,619
It's dirty. I washed it.

319
00:20:55,619 --> 00:20:57,519
What do you have in your hand?

320
00:20:57,519 --> 00:20:59,265
Nothing.

321
00:20:59,265 --> 00:21:01,173
Take it out and show me.

322
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:07,861
The other hand.

323
00:21:13,799 --> 00:21:16,341
Pay attention in class. I'm watching you.

324
00:21:18,680 --> 00:21:20,453
You're awake?

325
00:21:26,793 --> 00:21:28,359
Let's continue.

326
00:21:28,359 --> 00:21:29,380
Gao Yang.

327
00:21:29,380 --> 00:21:32,500
A groundless rumor.

328
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:33,700
A groundless rumor.

329
00:21:33,700 --> 00:21:38,849
It refers to unjustified news or rumor.

330
00:21:40,591 --> 00:21:43,640
Remember the idioms we talked about today and their usage.

331
00:21:43,640 --> 00:21:47,699
Review them or it'll be a waste of time teaching. Class dismissed.

332
00:21:47,699 --> 00:21:48,799
Gao Yang...

333
00:21:48,799 --> 00:21:50,539
Jin Beibei.

334
00:21:52,419 --> 00:21:53,880
What's wrong, Principal Jin?

335
00:21:53,880 --> 00:21:57,340
It's okay. You keep going. Come to my office.

336
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:04,019
What are you waiting for? Hurry up.

337
00:22:05,799 --> 00:22:07,467
Gao Yang...

338
00:22:07,467 --> 00:22:11,139
Hurry up. What gesture are you making?

339
00:22:12,350 --> 00:22:14,875
Beibei seems to have something to tell you.

340
00:22:16,319 --> 00:22:17,900
She has a little secret.

341
00:22:17,900 --> 00:22:20,020
Well,

342
00:22:20,020 --> 00:22:24,640
go flip through the little pocket in her backpack. There must be something in there.

343
00:22:24,640 --> 00:22:26,331
Go do it yourself.

344
00:22:27,270 --> 00:22:31,559
My legs are numb from sleeping in class. Hurry up.

345
00:23:00,870 --> 00:23:04,605
[Ye Xiaowen is Uncle Gao's illegitimate son! I heard it from my dad.]

346
00:23:08,019 --> 00:23:10,240
What is it?

347
00:23:16,559 --> 00:23:18,299
A photo sticker.

348
00:23:18,800 --> 00:23:24,500
What the hell? Is she crazy? What a psycho! How unconventional.

349
00:23:36,559 --> 00:23:40,880
Mr. Gao. Hello. My name is Ye Xiaowen.

350
00:23:41,720 --> 00:23:45,367
I'm Gao Bin, a PE teacher.

351
00:23:46,079 --> 00:23:48,739
Hello, Mr. Gao. I've been training for long-distance running for ten years.

352
00:23:48,739 --> 00:23:52,980
My score for the 10,000 m is one minute short of the standard for a Class I athlete.

353
00:23:52,980 --> 00:23:58,540
A few other kids from here are really good too. For example, Mi Jia. You can check them out as well.

354
00:23:58,540 --> 00:24:04,180
Xiaowen, I think you've misunderstood me. I'm not here to choose athletes.

355
00:24:04,180 --> 00:24:06,017
Actually,

356
00:24:07,599 --> 00:24:09,900
I'm a friend of your parents.

357
00:24:10,480 --> 00:24:14,159
I just heard about what happened to them recently

358
00:24:14,159 --> 00:24:16,435
and I learned about your situation.

359
00:24:17,140 --> 00:24:19,699
It must've been tough on you.

360
00:24:19,699 --> 00:24:23,579
I want to take you to Tieyuan and pay for your college fees.

361
00:24:23,579 --> 00:24:29,180
Of course, I know the children here basically want to go to military school or a teacher's university.

362
00:24:29,180 --> 00:24:33,280
But you're so talented. You should have more choices.

363
00:24:34,100 --> 00:24:38,320
Although Tieyuan is a small city,

364
00:24:38,320 --> 00:24:43,320
there are lots of competition opportunities. Guaranteed acceptance, bonus points, anything is possible.

365
00:24:46,559 --> 00:24:48,433
I still remember,

366
00:24:49,620 --> 00:24:52,479
your mom used to have good grades.

367
00:24:52,479 --> 00:24:54,359
She went to the Beijing University of Technology.

368
00:24:54,359 --> 00:24:58,279
But I believe you'll certainly do better than her.

369
00:24:59,160 --> 00:25:00,840
Thank you, that's all right.

370
00:25:00,840 --> 00:25:05,559
Xiaowen, I'm not looking to adopt you. I just want to help you. I really am your parents' friend.

371
00:25:05,559 --> 00:25:08,520
If I don't help you, it would feel bad for your mom and our friendship for so many years!

372
00:25:08,520 --> 00:25:10,096
Xiaowen,

373
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:12,879
you... you... You're leaving?

374
00:25:12,879 --> 00:25:15,500
Don't worry, I'm not leaving.

375
00:25:16,419 --> 00:25:18,806
Thank you, I really don't need it.

376
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:30,419
Come on, have a drumstick.

377
00:25:30,419 --> 00:25:33,340
Xiaowen, it will supplement your legs.
(T/N: a Chinese medicine ideology where eating an animal's body part will nourish the human's respective body part)

378
00:25:33,340 --> 00:25:35,080
What does that mean?

379
00:25:35,080 --> 00:25:37,380
Gao Bin, I'm still here.

380
00:25:37,380 --> 00:25:42,639
Xiaowen is a long-distance runner. Don't be so petty. Here, you'll eat this.

381
00:25:42,639 --> 00:25:46,499
This is fattier, chicken butt.

382
00:25:48,160 --> 00:25:50,000
You are favoring him too much.

383
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:53,220
I'm favoring him?

384
00:25:53,220 --> 00:25:56,040
I'm the best father in Tieyuan.

385
00:25:56,040 --> 00:25:57,672
Wait right here!

386
00:26:00,680 --> 00:26:04,880
Xiaowen, you can't eat both of them. Let me have one.

387
00:26:08,379 --> 00:26:11,419
You're taking his drumstick?

388
00:26:18,320 --> 00:26:20,320
Here, it's all fixed up.

389
00:26:22,140 --> 00:26:24,400
Did you really fix it?

390
00:26:32,640 --> 00:26:35,540
What do you mean by this? Who are you trying to fool?

391
00:26:36,720 --> 00:26:39,160
The Subor Games Machine, the kind with a hundred games on one disc.

392
00:26:39,160 --> 00:26:42,079
Wait, where's the one my mom bought me?

393
00:26:44,039 --> 00:26:46,479
That one... is beyond repair. I sold it.

394
00:26:46,479 --> 00:26:48,292
You sold it?

395
00:26:49,160 --> 00:26:50,908
Where's the money?

396
00:26:56,960 --> 00:26:58,960
All right, let's eat.

397
00:26:58,960 --> 00:27:04,319
After dinner, play it with Xiaowen for a while and relax a little. Work-life balance.

398
00:27:04,920 --> 00:27:07,440
I still need to play for a while with him?

399
00:27:08,599 --> 00:27:12,860
I see how it is. Your biological son should be Ye Xiaowen.

400
00:27:12,860 --> 00:27:14,560
That's nonsense.

401
00:27:14,560 --> 00:27:18,320
Nonsense? I'm speaking nonsense? He gets both drumsticks

402
00:27:18,320 --> 00:27:23,680
and I get the chicken butt! I asked you to fix this and you came back with this?

403
00:27:23,680 --> 00:27:27,459
I'm the orphan who isn't loved by anyone!

404
00:27:33,640 --> 00:27:35,060
Xiaowen.

405
00:27:35,060 --> 00:27:36,874
I'm full.

406
00:27:45,119 --> 00:27:50,519
- You...
- Hurry up. Go check on your real son.
- You are such a big mouth.

407
00:27:50,519 --> 00:27:53,858
- Come inside!
- What? I'm eating.

408
00:27:55,230 --> 00:27:57,510
Stand up! Hurry up.

409
00:27:59,450 --> 00:28:02,297
- What do you want?
- Be quiet.

410
00:28:09,559 --> 00:28:11,329
What are you doing?

411
00:28:11,329 --> 00:28:12,904
Sit down.

412
00:28:19,480 --> 00:28:21,959
Go on. What is it?

413
00:28:22,880 --> 00:28:25,000
From now on,

414
00:28:25,519 --> 00:28:28,920
I'm going to tell you a big secret.

415
00:28:29,580 --> 00:28:31,799
Keep your voice down. Do you hear me?

416
00:28:31,799 --> 00:28:33,557
Fine, fine.

417
00:28:35,960 --> 00:28:40,299
I wanted to tell you about this solemnly.

418
00:28:40,299 --> 00:28:46,680
But you kept mentioning "orphan" and "parentless". I was caught off guard.

419
00:28:47,319 --> 00:28:49,459
What about orphans?

420
00:28:49,459 --> 00:28:56,159
Anyway, from now on, don't mention that in front of Xiaowen again. Do you understand?

421
00:28:56,159 --> 00:28:58,349
Why can't I mention it?

422
00:28:58,349 --> 00:29:00,340
Is he an orphan?

423
00:29:08,259 --> 00:29:09,780
Xiaowen is an orphan?

424
00:29:09,780 --> 00:29:13,680
That's why you should be ashamed of your behavior.

425
00:29:13,680 --> 00:29:17,660
That can't be right. He's so arrogant. He doesn't seem like one at all.

426
00:29:17,660 --> 00:29:18,879
Are you telling the story or me?

427
00:29:18,879 --> 00:29:20,943
Go ahead. Go ahead.

428
00:29:34,699 --> 00:29:37,920
Xiaowen, have you decided on what to wish for on your birthday?

429
00:29:37,920 --> 00:29:43,419
- I want...
- Take it easy. Let's blow the candles first, then make a wish, okay?

430
00:29:49,940 --> 00:29:51,160
Let me see.

431
00:29:51,160 --> 00:29:52,595
Okay.

432
00:29:58,799 --> 00:30:00,720
Xiaowen, you have to think about it carefully.

433
00:30:00,720 --> 00:30:03,967
You only have one chance per year.

434
00:30:03,967 --> 00:30:07,900
Okay, I got it. I'll come down right away.

435
00:30:18,680 --> 00:30:20,481
What's wrong?

436
00:30:22,799 --> 00:30:27,260
There's been an accident at the drill site. We have to go check it out.

437
00:30:27,260 --> 00:30:29,037
Right now?

438
00:30:31,960 --> 00:30:35,659
Xiaowen, wait here for a while. Mom and dad need to go out for a bit.

439
00:30:35,659 --> 00:30:39,612
We'll be back to celebrate your birthday in a little while, okay?

440
00:30:39,612 --> 00:30:41,140
Good boy.

441
00:30:43,900 --> 00:30:47,240
Don't eat without us, Son. Wait for us.

442
00:30:47,240 --> 00:30:48,865
Be good.

443
00:30:52,900 --> 00:30:57,899
Xiaowen's parents were my childhood friends.

444
00:30:57,899 --> 00:31:00,519
They were exceptional.

445
00:31:01,440 --> 00:31:07,179
Later on, they went to another city and we lost contact.

446
00:31:07,179 --> 00:31:11,597
I always thought they would be really happy together.

447
00:31:11,597 --> 00:31:15,559
But I found out two years ago

448
00:31:15,559 --> 00:31:18,200
that his parents had an accident

449
00:31:18,839 --> 00:31:21,200
when Xiaowen was five years old

450
00:31:22,380 --> 00:31:24,680
and passed away.

451
00:31:25,519 --> 00:31:26,519
Is that true?

452
00:31:26,519 --> 00:31:28,319
Of course it is.

453
00:31:28,319 --> 00:31:31,400
Xiaowen grew up in an orphanage.

454
00:31:31,400 --> 00:31:36,019
It took me a lot of effort to convince him to come here with me.

455
00:31:37,400 --> 00:31:42,380
I'm not planning to adopt him. I just want to pay for his college.

456
00:31:42,380 --> 00:31:47,999
I've already told you to be nicer to Xiaowen. You just won't listen.

457
00:31:47,999 --> 00:31:50,659
- Why didn't you tell me earlier?
- How could I tell you?

458
00:31:50,659 --> 00:31:54,500
You're such a big mouth. If you tell people in school, then Xiaowen...

459
00:31:54,500 --> 00:31:58,287
How can Xiaowen still study in this school?

460
00:32:06,240 --> 00:32:10,657
By the way, that goes for Mi Jia too.

461
00:32:10,657 --> 00:32:16,839
Mi Jia was a pitiful child too. Her background is similar to Xiaowen's.

462
00:32:16,839 --> 00:32:19,019
- Mi Jia is an orphan too?
- Yes.

463
00:32:19,019 --> 00:32:22,459
That's why you should treat Mi Jia nicer, too.

464
00:32:25,550 --> 00:32:27,660
Mi Jia is an orphan, too.

465
00:32:28,580 --> 00:32:30,669
I have to process it for a while.

466
00:32:31,440 --> 00:32:33,519
That's too much information at once.

467
00:32:33,519 --> 00:32:36,580
Gao Yang, come out for a moment!

468
00:32:36,580 --> 00:32:39,240
I have something to tell you.

469
00:32:43,979 --> 00:32:47,300
Make sure you don't tell Beibei about this.

470
00:32:47,300 --> 00:32:50,319
You're the only one who knows in the school. Keep it confidential.

471
00:32:50,319 --> 00:32:53,719
Got it. You can have the drumstick.

472
00:33:08,259 --> 00:33:11,760
Gao Yang, did you see this?

473
00:33:11,760 --> 00:33:13,319
Yes.

474
00:33:17,380 --> 00:33:21,039
What do you think about Xiaowen?

475
00:33:21,039 --> 00:33:22,300
You know about it too?

476
00:33:22,300 --> 00:33:25,920
Of course. What did your dad say?

477
00:33:27,119 --> 00:33:29,279
My dad admitted it.

478
00:33:30,179 --> 00:33:34,799
I can't believe that happened to Xiaowen.

479
00:33:38,519 --> 00:33:41,340
It must've been a great shock to you.

480
00:33:43,219 --> 00:33:45,359
Are you upset?

481
00:33:46,820 --> 00:33:48,893
It's normal.

482
00:33:48,893 --> 00:33:51,619
When my mom was pregnant with Doudou, I asked her what happened.

483
00:33:51,619 --> 00:33:53,799
She said she gained weight and would be better in a few days.

484
00:33:53,799 --> 00:33:57,360
Suddenly, she came home with Doudou in her arms and told me I'm the elder sister.

485
00:33:57,360 --> 00:33:58,880
Why should I?

486
00:33:58,880 --> 00:34:02,060
That's right. Why? Why did something like that happen to Xiaowen?

487
00:34:02,060 --> 00:34:04,160
That's really common.

488
00:34:04,160 --> 00:34:05,640
I really understand how you feel.

489
00:34:05,640 --> 00:34:10,520
I can't even accept Doudou when we have the same mother.

490
00:34:10,520 --> 00:34:13,839
It's... It's so unfair to ask you to accept Xiaowen.

491
00:34:13,839 --> 00:34:15,610
It's too hard.

492
00:34:16,953 --> 00:34:19,080
Wait, how should I treat him?

493
00:34:19,080 --> 00:34:21,939
His background is too unique.

494
00:34:21,939 --> 00:34:25,019
Well, you... What should I say?

495
00:34:25,019 --> 00:34:28,780
My dad didn't make such a big mistake back then.

496
00:34:32,520 --> 00:34:34,440
Hello, Dean.

497
00:34:34,440 --> 00:34:39,599
Xiaowen? It's so late now. What can I do for you?

498
00:34:41,440 --> 00:34:44,400
I... I just want to ask...

499
00:34:44,960 --> 00:34:50,159
What's the relationship between Mr. Gao and my parents?

500
00:34:50,159 --> 00:34:55,240
Weren't they classmates? What's wrong? Why do you ask?

501
00:34:55,240 --> 00:34:58,319
I... I'm just asking. It's okay.

502
00:34:58,319 --> 00:35:02,000
Did you encounter any problems?

503
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:07,860
No, no. I'm doing great here. Don't worry. Well,

504
00:35:07,860 --> 00:35:12,079
when I'm in college, I have time to get a part-time job. I'll be able to send money back to the orphanage.

505
00:35:12,079 --> 00:35:15,240
Xiaowen, you're still a child.

506
00:35:15,240 --> 00:35:19,820
You have to focus on your study. Don't give yourself too much pressure.

507
00:35:19,820 --> 00:35:24,279
The orphanage is fine. Don't worry about it.

508
00:35:24,279 --> 00:35:25,854
Okay.

509
00:35:26,599 --> 00:35:29,160
- Bye, Dean.
- Bye.

510
00:35:44,939 --> 00:35:46,639
I've made a decision.

511
00:35:46,639 --> 00:35:48,700
You made a decision?

512
00:35:49,519 --> 00:35:51,639
Don't do anything extreme.

513
00:35:51,639 --> 00:35:53,645
I want to be nice to Xiaowen.

514
00:35:53,645 --> 00:35:56,986
I want to treat him like my own brother, closer than my own brother.

515
00:35:59,199 --> 00:36:00,480
Why are you so generous?

516
00:36:00,480 --> 00:36:02,326
Is this the first day we met?

517
00:36:04,340 --> 00:36:06,740
Gao Yang, don't make yourself suffer.

518
00:36:06,740 --> 00:36:09,440
The two of you don't have the same mother.

519
00:36:09,440 --> 00:36:11,559
So what if we don't have the same mother?

520
00:36:11,559 --> 00:36:15,120
I believe no man would care about something like that.

521
00:36:19,719 --> 00:36:21,312
By the way,

522
00:36:24,260 --> 00:36:27,960
you have to keep Xiaowen's matter a secret for me.

523
00:36:27,960 --> 00:36:33,080
I don't want people to look at him differently. Can you do that?

524
00:36:33,080 --> 00:36:35,960
Gao Yang, you are so awesome.

525
00:36:46,880 --> 00:36:51,439
Xiaowen, the weather is dry. Eat more fruit.

526
00:37:05,840 --> 00:37:07,618
Well,

527
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:12,355
Gao Yang

528
00:37:12,355 --> 00:37:15,999
just likes to talk nonsense. Don't mind him.

529
00:37:18,800 --> 00:37:23,199
I can tell that Gao Yang likes you a lot.

530
00:37:23,199 --> 00:37:27,520
He just likes to run his mouth. Don't take it to heart.

531
00:37:27,520 --> 00:37:29,119
I didn't.

532
00:37:29,119 --> 00:37:31,419
That's good.

533
00:37:33,440 --> 00:37:35,820
You don't know me too well.

534
00:37:35,820 --> 00:37:41,379
I like to be frank and honest. I usually speak my mind.

535
00:37:41,379 --> 00:37:46,599
If anything makes you uncomfortable, just tell me.

536
00:37:49,880 --> 00:37:51,519
What did you say?

537
00:37:51,519 --> 00:37:56,159
Why did they call me your illegitimate son? You're not my parents' friend!

538
00:38:05,679 --> 00:38:08,839
No, I'm just a bit tired.

539
00:38:08,839 --> 00:38:11,451
All right. Get some rest soon.

540
00:38:11,451 --> 00:38:13,519
Wait, Mr. Gao.

541
00:38:15,360 --> 00:38:16,913
What is it?

542
00:38:17,630 --> 00:38:20,319
You just simply want to help me, right?

543
00:38:20,319 --> 00:38:21,599
Yes.

544
00:38:21,599 --> 00:38:24,319
Since you and my parents were close friends,

545
00:38:24,319 --> 00:38:27,199
why haven't you contacted them for so many years?

546
00:38:27,199 --> 00:38:28,400
Because your mother and I...

547
00:38:28,400 --> 00:38:30,136
What was it?

548
00:38:30,740 --> 00:38:33,130
I didn't contact them for so long because...

549
00:38:35,239 --> 00:38:36,240
Tell me.

550
00:38:36,240 --> 00:38:41,420
Grown-ups are really complicated. You kids won't understand.

551
00:38:45,740 --> 00:38:49,319
What did you say about me out there?

552
00:38:49,319 --> 00:38:52,700
I said you're my friend's child

553
00:38:52,700 --> 00:38:56,359
and you'll temporarily stay here until you go to college.

554
00:39:01,060 --> 00:39:02,000
T-That's all?

555
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:03,625
That's all.

556
00:39:05,700 --> 00:39:09,640
Think again. Is there anything else you haven't told me?

557
00:39:09,640 --> 00:39:12,179
Anything I haven't told you?

558
00:39:18,000 --> 00:39:20,579
No.

559
00:39:27,380 --> 00:39:29,139
Xiaowen,

560
00:39:31,800 --> 00:39:34,039
you know everything?

561
00:39:35,800 --> 00:39:38,519
Gao Yang sleepwalks.

562
00:39:38,519 --> 00:39:40,315
Please excuse him.

563
00:39:41,499 --> 00:39:43,447
Go to bed soon.

564
00:40:21,890 --> 00:40:27,930
♫ I know the direction of dawn ♫

565
00:40:27,930 --> 00:40:35,227
♫ It's right in front of me, waiting for me to shine ♫

566
00:40:35,227 --> 00:40:41,285
♫  The starlight that shines alone the way  ♫

567
00:40:41,285 --> 00:40:47,225
♫ Accompanying me on my adventure packing my dreams into my heart ♫

568
00:40:47,225 --> 00:40:53,777
♫  I don't fear the rough journey ahead, I will no longer run away  ♫

569
00:40:53,777 --> 00:40:59,540
♫  Maybe I'm not destined for the hardship of this journey  ♫

570
00:40:59,540 --> 00:41:03,404
♫  And chase after the longing in my heart  ♫

571
00:41:03,404 --> 00:41:06,770
♫  Let set sail on our dreams  ♫

572
00:41:06,770 --> 00:41:10,240
♫  Let's not have any regrets in our youth  ♫

573
00:41:10,247 --> 00:41:16,907
♫  Even if you stumble and fall, I'll be by your side  ♫

574
00:41:16,907 --> 00:41:20,318
♫  Let's find the answer through the madness  ♫

575
00:41:20,318 --> 00:41:24,330
♫  Let's have courage to ride the waves and billows  ♫

576
00:41:24,330 --> 00:41:28,150
♫  With my wings, I'll fly us to the future  ♫

577
00:41:28,150 --> 00:41:35,710
♫  And step forward into the future without fear of sorrow  ♫
